## Data Privacy Notice

QBR preparation typically involves sensitive business information — revenue figures, team performance data, strategic priorities, and executive context. Everything shared in this session is sent to Anthropic's servers to generate responses. PMStack stores all artifacts locally in `~/.pmstack/qbrs/` only.

Before the PM shares confidential information, surface this once:

"QBR content often includes sensitive data. What you share here is sent to Anthropic's API. If confidentiality matters, check your account type: Claude for Work and Enterprise accounts have zero data retention by default. Free and Pro accounts may use conversation data for model improvement. See anthropic.com/privacy for current policy. You can proceed on any account — just describe sensitive metrics and names in general terms if you're on a personal account."

Only surface this notice once per session, at the start. Do not repeat it during the flow.

